________________________________________
Pillar 1 — Agent Loop
This is your runtime orchestration layer.
while (!done) {
    analyze()
    decide()
    callTool()
    evaluate()
}
Stop Conditions
MAX_ITERATIONS = 5
MAX_COST = 0.25
MAX_RUNTIME = 20s
If exceeded:
{
  "alarm": "AGENT_LIMIT_EXCEEDED"
}
This shows the harness controlling the LLM.
________________________________________
Pillar 2 — Tools
The model needs "hands."
Tool 1
Portfolio Analyzer
analyzePortfolio()
Returns:
{
  "largestHolding": "AAPL",
  "allocation": 18
}
________________________________________
Tool 2
Risk Calculator
calculateRisk()
Returns:
{
  "riskScore": 82
}
________________________________________
Tool 3
Market Data
getMarketData("NVDA")
Returns:
{
  "volatility": "HIGH"
}
________________________________________
Tool Contract
interface Tool {
   name: string
   schema: JSONSchema
   execute(input): Result
}
________________________________________
Pillar 3 — Guardrails
These happen BEFORE execution.
Maximum Trade Size
{
  "name": "MAX_TRADE_SIZE",
  "limit": 50000
}
________________________________________
Approved Securities
{
  "name": "APPROVED_SECURITIES"
}
Only:
AAPL
MSFT
NVDA
GOOGL
________________________________________
Retirement Account Restrictions
{
  "name": "RETIREMENT_ACCOUNT"
}
Reject:
Options
Margin
Leverage
________________________________________
Human Approval Guardrail
If:
Trade > $25,000
Require:
Manual Approval
This satisfies the challenge's human-in-the-loop recommendation.
________________________________________
Pillar 4 — Checkpoints
The challenge explicitly requires pass/fail checkpoints.
Checkpoint 1
Concentration Risk
Pass if:
Position < 20%
Result:
{
  "checkpoint": "CONCENTRATION",
  "passed": false
}
________________________________________
Checkpoint 2
Risk Score
Pass if:
Risk Score < 80
________________________________________
Checkpoint 3
Agent Confidence
Pass if:
Confidence > 70%
________________________________________
Checkpoint 4
Liquidity
Pass if:
Average Daily Volume > Threshold
________________________________________
Material Handling
Challenge requirement.
Input Normalization
Input:
{
  "request": "Buy 40k NVDA"
}
Normalize:
{
  "action": "BUY",
  "ticker": "NVDA",
  "amount": 40000
}
________________________________________
Output Standardization
Every stage emits:
{
  "runId": "...",
  "stage": "...",
  "status": "...",
  "timestamp": "..."
}
________________________________________
Alarms
The challenge specifically wants structured alarms.
Alarm Structure
{
  "type": "",
  "severity": "",
  "context": {},
  "recommended_action": ""
}
________________________________________
Example 1
{
  "type": "POSITION_CONCENTRATION",
  "severity": "HIGH",
  "context": {
    "ticker": "NVDA",
    "allocation": "34%"
  },
  "recommended_action": "Reduce position size"
}
________________________________________
Example 2
{
  "type": "RISK_SCORE_EXCEEDED",
  "severity": "CRITICAL",
  "context": {
    "score": 92
  },
  "recommended_action": "Reject trade"
}
________________________________________
Example 3
{
  "type": "LOW_CONFIDENCE",
  "severity": "MEDIUM",
  "context": {
    "confidence": 0.48
  },
  "recommended_action": "Escalate to human"
}
