Observability (Your Secret Weapon)
Although not a required pillar in the brief, it can be your differentiator.
Instrument everything with:
OpenTelemetry
Trace:
Run
 ├── Guardrail
 ├── Agent
 ├── Tool Call
 ├── Checkpoint
 ├── Alarm
 └── Decision
Capture:
Latency
Token Usage
Cost
Retries
Checkpoint Results
Alarm Counts
Tool Success %
Dashboard:
p95 latency
$/trade
alarm frequency
checkpoint failure %
agent confidence
________________________________________
Swappable Agent Design
One of the strongest "Should" requirements.
interface TradeAgent {
   analyze(input): TradeRecommendation
}
Implement:
OpenAITradeAgent
ClaudeTradeAgent
Switch with:
AGENT_PROVIDER=openai
No harness code changes.
________________________________________
Demo Flow (5 Minutes)
1.	User requests: "Buy $40,000 NVDA."
2.	Material handler normalizes request.
3.	Agent recommends BUY.
4.	Tools calculate risk.
5.	Concentration checkpoint fails.
6.	Alarm fires.
7.	Trade blocked.
8.	User reduces amount to $10,000.
9.	Checkpoints pass.
10.	Trade approved.
11.	Swap OpenAI agent with another agent.
12.	Same harness still works.

